                                   VIOLENT PERFECTION



          (What good is knowledge,
                 if it gives no power to the wise...)




Disclaimer:    Neither the author nor the group are
          responsible for any rights and/or wrongs resultant
          from the use of this article. The following
          composition is an exercise in theoretical
          application of military tactics to modern urban
          centers.




     TERRORISM (SCENARIO):   4-TUNNELS
                                    (viper015)

BY Maradonna

Main Goal:     Simultaneous destruction or partial
     incapacitation of the 4 NYC tunnels (Lincoln, Holland,
     Queens Midtown and Brooklyn Battery).

Secondary Goals:
     1. Heightened levels of fright and panic.
     2. Dissemination of such hysteria through Media
          manipulation.
     3. A show of force.

Requirements/Tools:
     a) 4 (four) Mini-vans with darkened side and back
          windows.
     b) 4 (four) Motorcycles (2-seaters).
     c) 4 (four) Explosive devices of middle- to low-grade
          potency with radio-controlled and timeing triggers
          on each.

Human Resources:    a) 4 (four) drivers for the Mini-vans.
                    b) 4 (four) drivers for the Motorcycles.

Description:   4 (four) Mini-vans, one for each tunnel
     (Lincoln, Holland, Queens Midtown, Brooklyn Battery),
     enter them from Manhattan on a weekend morning. 4 (four)
     motorcycles go right after each Mini-van.

     Approximately at the middle of each tunnel, the Mini-
     vans will stop, their drivers will get out and onto the
     backseats of the motorcycles and drive away.

     The bombs will have 2 (two) triggers: a radio and a
     timer. A timer will be set to explode 1 minute (60
     seconds) after being engaged (and will be activated by
     the Mini-vans' drivers upon stopover. However, the
     timers will play the role of backups.

     Upon riding a motorcycle (from backseat) the Mini-vans'
     drivers will activate the radio detonators while at a
     distance of 100 to 200 meters from the vans (to prevent
     radio-signal loss).

     It is suggested that 7 to 10 blocks away from the
     tunnels both the drivers of the motorcycles and the
     Mini-vans should dispose of their motorcycles and
     disappear.

     A general telephoned warning to a few major Television
     Stations and Newspapers about an oncoming attack is
     advisable, but should not in any way give information as
     to the nature of the attack.  Also, such warning should
     be made not earlier than 10 to 15 minutes before the
     start of operation.

     A statement of fact and responsibility should be made
     not later than 5 minutes of the attack to the same
     stations.

Result:   The tunnels will be closed for at least 3-4 days
     (in case of light damage), and 8-12 days (in case of a
     moderate damage). Resulting heavy traffic, partial fear
     to drive over or under anything that is not dry, and
     hysteria can be further exploited by manipulation of
     Media with very little risk.




                                   June 4th, 1995.




